inistrators     Help     Sandbox     Recent Changes                          in: 1642 births, 1769 deaths, Blue-eyed individuals,     and 8 more    Breeders   Bronze Chocolate Frog Cards   Centenarians   Historical figures   Magizoologists   Males   Nobility   Wizards             English     Deutsch   Español   Suomi   Français   Italiano   Polski   Русский               Stoddard Withers              View source                         History                         Talk (1)                                         Stoddard Withers   Biographical information  Born 1642[1]   Died 1769 (aged 126-127)[2][3]   Title(s) Lord[2][3]    Physical information  Species Human[2][3]   Gender Male[2][3]   Hair colour Grey[2][3]   Eye colour Blue[2][3]   Skin colour White[2][3]    Affiliation  Occupation Magizoologist[2][3]   Loyalty Withers family   [Source]  Lord Stoddard Withers (1642 – 1769) was a wizard and Magizoologist who bred Winged horses. He created a sport that combined elements of polo and Quidditch, which was played on Winged horses instead of broomsticks. The sport never became popular though.[2][3]  Etymology The English word "withers" refers to the back of a horse, specifically between the shoulder-blades (at which place winged horses' wings can be expected to be found).  Appearances The Harry Potter Wiki has 4 images related to Stoddard Withers. Harry Potter and the Philosopher's Stone (video game) (Appears on a Famous Wizard Card) Harry Potter and the Chamber of Secrets (video game) (Appears on a Famous Wizard Card) Pottermore Notes and references   ↑ According to  Pottermore he was born in 1672 (Timeline).  ↑ 2.0 2.1 2.2 2.3 2.4 2.5 2.6 2.7 2.8 Harry Potter and the Philosopher's Stone (video game)  ↑ 3.0 3.1 3.2 3.3 3.4 3.5 3.6 3.7 3.8 Harry Potter and the Chamber of Secrets (video game)       Chocolate Frog Cards     Gold cards   Armando Dippet · Albus Dumbledore · Barberus Bragge · Bertie Bott · Carlotta Pinkstone · Dzou Yen · Falco Aesalon · Godric Gryffindo